[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/404724856","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/703#issuecomment-404724856","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/703","id":404724856,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwNDcyNDg1Ng==","user":{"login":"SergioBenitez","id":1480321,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0ODAzMjE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1480321?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez","html_url":"https://github.com/SergioBenitez","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-07-13T04:51:33Z","updated_at":"2018-07-13T04:51:33Z","body":"> Ran the rocket 'hello world' example on my Debian Stretch and none of the emojis are showing up properly\r\n\r\nIt's likely that you don't have a font with emoji support installed and/or your terminal doesn't support unicode. I'd suggest installing a font with emoji support. This isn't an issue with Rocket as much as it is with your environment.\r\n\r\n>  I would suggest that ANSI should be an optional feature and should be disabled by default. ...much of the important logging is displayed in white text on a white background.\r\n\r\nPresumably you mean coloring? I find colored logs helpful, just like I find syntax highlighting helpful: they help me distinguish between classes of information on the screen. As such, I don't foresee disabling coloring by default.\r\n\r\nThe argument that we shouldn't be explicitly using \"white\" or \"black\" colors because these are common background colors is interesting. On the one hand, I argue that this is a configuration issue: a user with a white terminal background shouldn't configure \"white\" to be the same color as their background. On the other hand, changing uses of \"white\" in Rocket to be the \"neutral\" color (usually white on black backgrounds and black on white backgrounds) might be a simpler solution that makes more people happy.\r\n\r\nAnother alternative solution is to provide a configuration option for disabling colors, say `ROCKET_COLORS=off` or similar. I'm not immediately opposed to this solution, either.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/404724856/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"SergioBenitez","id":1480321,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0ODAzMjE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1480321?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez","html_url":"https://github.com/SergioBenitez","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/events{/privacy}","received_event